TestOutputWriteHasNoSpuriousChannel
/ Drift case 1 — the load-bearing reason this branch exists.
/
/ Step text `- write out %message%` (from Tests/Simple/Start.goal:5) carries no
/ channel clause. With per-action notes (os/system/modules/output/write.notes.md)
/ carrying the channel routing rule only when output.write is in the planner's
/ set, the LLM should emit:
/   parameters: { Data: %message% }   (no channel key)
/   formal contains output.write(Data=%message%) and no `channel=` token.
/
/ Pre-fix shape that this test forbids:
/   formal='output.write(Data=%message%, channel=%!data%)'  -- forbidden
/   any 'channel' key in parameters with a %!data% value    -- forbidden
/
/ This test reads the last-built start.pr for Tests/Simple and asserts on its
/ content. The architect's verification rule (3 fresh-cache builds in a row)
/ runs externally:
/   rm -rf Tests/Simple/.build
/   ../PlangConsole/bin/Debug/net10.0/plang build /Tests/Simple   # then this test  (x3)
- read file '/Tests/Simple/.build/start.pr', write to %pr%
- assert %pr% contains '"text": "write out %message%"'
- assert %pr% does not contain 'channel=%!data%'
- assert %pr% does not contain '"name": "channel"'
